<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="209" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
4.6.5.4. 
<taxonomicName LSID="http://zoobank.org/1F02BE7E-315D-49F5-8F62-5C4CE0B7B1B8" authority="Djernæs &amp; Murienne, 2022" authorityName="Djernæs &amp; Murienne" authorityYear="2022" family="Blattidae" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" status="trib. nov." tribe="Celatoblattini">Celatoblattini</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="0" pageNumber="209">trib. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="209" type="type-genus">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Type-genus.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Johns, 1966.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="209" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
See 
<bibRefCitation author="Johns, P" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Canterbury Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="93 - 136" refId="B30" refString="Johns, P, 1966. The Cockroaches of New Zealand. Records of the Canterbury Museum 8: 93 - 136" title="The Cockroaches of New Zealand." volume="8" year="1966">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Johns’">Johns'</normalizedToken>
(1966)
</bibRefCitation>
diagnosis for genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
<bibRefCitation author="Johns, P" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Canterbury Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="93 - 136" refId="B30" refString="Johns, P, 1966. The Cockroaches of New Zealand. Records of the Canterbury Museum 8: 93 - 136" title="The Cockroaches of New Zealand." volume="8" year="1966">Johns (1966)</bibRefCitation>
erected the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for a number of blattid cockroaches found in New Zealand and placed it in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1810" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Blattinae">Blattinae</taxonomicName>
based on general habitus and the appearance of the legs. On the other hand, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="511 - 575" refId="B53" refString="Mackerras, MJ, 1968a. Australian Blattidae (Blattodea) IX. Revision of the Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae. Australian Journal of Zoology 16 (3): 511 - 575, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea) IX. Revision of the Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" volume="16" year="1968 a">Mackerras (1968a)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tepper" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Temnelytra" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Temnelytra" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Temnelytra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Methanini">Methanini</taxonomicName>
). It should be noted that 
<bibRefCitation author="Johns, P" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Canterbury Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="93 - 136" refId="B30" refString="Johns, P, 1966. The Cockroaches of New Zealand. Records of the Canterbury Museum 8: 93 - 136" title="The Cockroaches of New Zealand." volume="8" year="1966">Johns (1966)</bibRefCitation>
stated that his 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Alfken" baseAuthorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta brunni" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta brunni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not the same species as 
<bibRefCitation author="McKittrick, FA" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Cornell University Agricultural Experiment Station" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="1 - 197" refId="B56" refString="McKittrick, FA, 1964. Evolutionary studies of cockroaches. Memoirs of the Cornell University Agricultural Experiment Station 389: 1 - 197" title="Evolutionary studies of cockroaches." volume="389" year="1964">
<normalizedToken originalValue="McKittrick’s">McKittrick's</normalizedToken>
(1964)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alfken" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Platyzosteria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platyzosteria brunni" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Platyzosteria brunni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see 4.6.5.1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
<bibRefCitation author="Princis, K" journalOrPublisher="The Natural History of Rennell Island, British Solomon Islands" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="31 - 37" refId="B69" refString="Princis, K, 1970. Blattarien von den Inseln Rennell und Bellona. The Natural History of Rennell Island, British Solomon Islands 6: 31 - 37" title="Blattarien von den Inseln Rennell und Bellona." volume="6" year="1970">Princis (1970</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Princis, K" editor="Beier, M" journalOrPublisher="W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="1041 - 1224" refId="B70" refString="Princis, K, 1971. Blattariae: Subordo Epilamproidea. Fam.: Ectobiidae. In: Beier, M, Ed., Orthopterorum Catalogus, Pars 14. W. Junk, 's-Gravenhage: 1041 - 1224" title="Blattariae: Subordo Epilamproidea. Fam.: Ectobiidae." volumeTitle="Orthopterorum Catalogus, Pars 14." year="1971">1971</bibRefCitation>
) included several species from Australia and New Guinea in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, making 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mackerras" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Austrostylopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Austrostylopyga" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Austrostylopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a junior synonym, and also added several species from New Caledonia. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu Princis was polyphyletic in all our analyses, split into three widely separated groups. One of these groups corresponds to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu Johns as it only contains species from New Zealand (here 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta vulgaris" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. CK77, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. CK109). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu Johns is a coherent phylogenetic group and forms a distinctive lineage (Chinn and Gemmel 2004; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3390/insects2030369" author="Goldberg, J" journalOrPublisher="Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="369 - 399" refId="B24" refString="Goldberg, J, Trewick, SA, 2011. Exploring phylogeographic congruence in a continental island system. Insects 2 (3): 369 - 399, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3390/insects2030369" title="Exploring phylogeographic congruence in a continental island system." url="https://doi.org/10.3390/insects2030369" volume="2" year="2011">Goldberg and Trewick 2011</bibRefCitation>
; this paper), including 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. brunni" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="species" species="brunni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">C. brunni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was included in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Princis" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Maoriblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maoriblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Maoriblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Princis, K" editor="Beier, M" journalOrPublisher="W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="402 - 614" refId="B67" refString="Princis, K, 1966. Blattariae: Subordo Blattoidea. Fam.: Blattidae, Nocticolidae. In: Beier, M, Ed., Orthopterorum Catalogus, Pars 8. W. Junk, 's-Gravenhage: 402 - 614" title="Blattariae: Subordo Blattoidea. Fam.: Blattidae, Nocticolidae." volumeTitle="Orthopterorum Catalogus, Pars 8." year="1966">Princis (1966</bibRefCitation>
: p. 543), although Princis later (1967: p. 710) changed this in his corrections and placed 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. brunni" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="species" species="brunni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">C. brunni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We will henceforth refer to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu Johns as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.s. In our analyses, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.s. was consistently placed within 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
as sister to 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Polyzosteriini">Polyzosteriini</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Djernæs &amp; Murienne" authorityYear="2022" family="Blattidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Rothisilphini">Rothisilphini</taxonomicName>
. Thus, we move 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.s. from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1810" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Blattinae">Blattinae</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
, and place it in a separate tribe, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Djernæs &amp; Murienne" authorityYear="2022" family="Blattidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Celatoblattini">Celatoblattini</taxonomicName>
, so far consisting only of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.s. See section 4.6.5.1. for our reasons for not including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Djernæs &amp; Murienne" authorityYear="2022" family="Blattidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Celatoblattini">Celatoblattini</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Djernæs &amp; Murienne" authorityYear="2022" family="Blattidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Rothisilphini">Rothisilphini</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="tribe" tribe="Polyzosteriini">Polyzosteriini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
